item.title: Missing Symbol?
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

[quote=“Coont, post:3, topic:545161”][quote author=sk8rdude461 link=topic=664042.msg4438535#msg4438535 date=1405823849]
It means what it says, literally.
It cannot find the symbol (variable) altarID.

altarID looks like it’s an array of integers,

so it’d go in the Runecrafting class (wherever the getRunecrafting is pointed to)

and would probably look like

public int[] altarID = {
0, 1, 3, 458376, 4836
};

The data is fake, but I hope you get the idea.
[/quote]
Simpleton terms please. I really just don’t understand. Would you like to see the code?[/quote]

That was really, really simple terms. I don’t know how basic you expect.
http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/index.html
Please read that ^^ link. The links in it and below this text will really help you…

http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/variables.html
^If you don’t know what a variable is.

http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/datatypes.html
^Primitive datatypes (things like int, String, etc)

http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/arrays.html
^Arrays. This you may want to read since you’re working with one right now.
